    <id>https://www.strangerfoods.org/recipes/chinese-bbq-pork-noodle-soup</id>
    <title>Chinese BBQ pork noodle soup</title>
    <updated>2026-05-10T16:39:39.243016+00:00</updated>
    <content type="html">&lt;h1 style="text-align:center;font-family:sans-serif;"&gt;Chinese BBQ pork noodle soup&lt;/h1&gt;
        &lt;br&gt;
        &lt;img src="https://www.strangerfoods.org/images/chinese-bbq-pork-noodle-soup.webp" style="text-align:center;"/&gt;
        &lt;br&gt;
        &lt;p style="font-family:sans-serif;&gt;BBQ pork, known as Char Siu, is one of the most popular Guangdong dishes and goes well with rice or noodles. For a really tasty dish, marinate the pork well in advance so that the flavours penetrate the meat.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
