  <entry>
    <id>https://www.strangerfoods.org/recipes/lamb-courgette-and-orange-stir-fry</id>
    <title>Lamb, courgette &amp; orange stir-fry</title>
    <updated>2026-05-10T16:39:39.242210+00:00</updated>
    <content type="html">&lt;h1 style="text-align:center;font-family:sans-serif;"&gt;Lamb, courgette &amp; orange stir-fry&lt;/h1&gt;
        &lt;br&gt;
        &lt;img src="https://www.strangerfoods.org/images/lamb-courgette-and-orange-stir-fry.webp" style="text-align:center;"/&gt;
        &lt;br&gt;
        &lt;p style="font-family:sans-serif;&gt;This dish is light and, with the use of orange and its juice, is fresh-tasting with a touch of citrus sweetness. Traditionally, lamb stir-fries are served with broccoli or asparagus, but here I give it a modern make-over, using courgette instead. The secret to making a delicious stir-fry in minutes is to slice the lamb thinly. It takes less time to cook and the succulent texture is preserved.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://www.strangerfoods.org/recipes/lamb-courgette-and-orange-stir-fry"/>
